html:div.style:
margin: 1em 0 1em 0.25em;
padding: 0.5em 1.1em 0.5em 1.2em;
border-left: 4px solid rgba(90, 90, 110, 0.7);
border-radius: var(--radius);
background-color: rgba(90, 90, 110, 0.05);

margin: 1em 0 1em 0.25em;
padding: 0.5em 1.1em 0.5em 1.2em;
border-left: 4px solid rgba(60, 90, 180, 0.8);
border-radius: var(--radius);
background-color: rgba(60, 90, 180, 0.05);

html:div.html:pre:
struct A {
    virtual void f();
    int a;
};

struct B {
    virtual void g();
    int b;
};

struct D : A, B {
    void g() override;   // overrides B::g
    int d;
};

html:div.style:
margin: 1em 0 1em 0.25em;
padding: 0.5em 1.1em 0.5em 1.2em;
border-left: 4px solid rgba(60, 90, 180, 0.8);
border-radius: var(--radius);
background-color: rgba(60, 90, 180, 0.05);

fr:mainmatter.html:div:
Example. 
Consider the following class hierarchy:
struct Base {
    virtual void f();
    virtual void g();
    int x;
};

struct Derived : Base {
    void f() override;   // overrides Base::f
    void h();            // non-virtual, not in vtable
    int y;
};
This yields the following components for each type of object:
Base object:        Derived object:
[ vptr ]            [ vptr ]      → points to Derived's vtable
[ x    ]            [ x    ]
                    [ y    ]

html:div.style:
margin: 1em 0 1em 0.25em;
padding: 0.5em 1.1em 0.5em 1.2em;
border-left: 4px solid rgba(90, 90, 110, 0.7);
border-radius: var(--radius);
background-color: rgba(90, 90, 110, 0.05);

margin: 1em 0 1em 0.25em;
padding: 0.5em 1.1em 0.5em 1.2em;
border-left: 4px solid rgba(200, 55, 45, 0.85);
border-radius: var(--radius);
background-color: rgba(200, 55, 45, 0.06);

fr:mainmatter.html:div:
Problem. 
  You can only read the active member of a union.
union U { int i; float f; };
U u;
u.i = 42;
float x = u.f;  // UB — reading the inactive member

html:div.style:
margin: 1em 0 1em 0.25em;
padding: 0.5em 1.1em 0.5em 1.2em;
border-left: 4px solid rgba(200, 55, 45, 0.85);
border-radius: var(--radius);
background-color: rgba(200, 55, 45, 0.06);

margin: 1em 0 1em 0.25em;
padding: 0.5em 1.1em 0.5em 1.2em;
border-left: 4px solid rgba(90, 90, 110, 0.7);
border-radius: var(--radius);
background-color: rgba(90, 90, 110, 0.05);

fr:mainmatter.html:div:
Remark. 
Avoid "naked" unions; opt for "tagged" unions.
struct Value {
    enum class Type { Int, Float, Str } tag;
    union {
        int   i;
        float f;
        char  s[32];
    };
};
This along with lifetime management is the basis of std::variant.

